sub_questions.question_text:
(a) A function $g$ is defined on the set of real numbers, $R$, by $g(x) = \frac{1+3x}{x-1}, \ x \neq 1$. Find:
i) image of $-1$ under the function $g$;
ii) value of $x$ for which $g(x) = 7$;
iii) value of $g(-3)$;

(b) The sum of the first ten terms of an Arithmetic Progression (A.P) is $120$. If the fifth term is $6$ less than the eighth; find the:
i) common difference;
ii) first term;
